summary: Vinesh, a customer of chocolate company Itsy Bitsy, calls M customer support regarding a disappointing experience with a recent order. Vinesh explains that the order, consisting of a chocolate ganache, was filled with fungus and was not up to standard. M assures Vinesh that they will file a complaint on his behalf and requests his personal details to identify his account, which includes his email address (dinesh@gmail.com), address in Bangalore, and phone number. Itsy Bitsy then asks for the batch number of the chocolate to further investigate the matter, to which Vinesh provides the details. The customer service agent acknowledges the issue and offers to connect Vinesh with the marketing team to further address the matter. Vinesh agrees, and the call ends with thanks from both parties.
speaker_a_summary: Ikram from M is assisting a customer who ordered chocolate from their location but was disappointed with the state it arrived in. Ikram files a complaint on their behalf and collects details including their name (Vinesh), email (Double 92 at Gmail.com), address, and phone number. The chocolate was ordered online, and the customer believes the temperature may have affected the state of the chocolate. Ikram collects additional details about the product including its name (Itsy Bitsy), and potential batch number, date, and MRP. The customer is satisfied with the resolution and will be contacted soon for further follow-up.
speaker_b_summary: The narrator is disappointed with their order of a chocolate ganache, which they had ordered using the Zat platform. The order was placed by their wife, and they cannot provide their email address or address for a refund or replacement. The chocolate arrived at room temperature and was full of fungus. It is not worth INR 1000 and does not seem safe to consume. The narrator reminds themselves to be more careful with their online orders in the future.
cohere_points:
- Customer complaints about a faulty Itsy Bitsy chocolate order and hopes to file a complaint
- Agent helps collect information about the order and tells the customer they will file a complaint but might need more details
- The customer provides their address and email and describes the problem in more detail
